description:
"We are closed for VACATION."

Geez! If only I too could go on vacation as often as the owners of Golden Gate Bakery. This place randomly shuts down for literally months on end. In fact, their schedule is so notoriously erratic that there is a website solely dedicated to monitoring it. Here you go: http://www.is-the-golden-gate-bakery-open-today.com/

On the off chance that you are able to catch them open, prepare yourself for a test of patience. Do you see the line of people that wraps down the street and stretches all the way back up? Yep, get queueing!

// Egg Tart - 4 stars
Golden Gate Bakery's signature pastry comes with a generous amount of custard and a perfectly flaky crust. It has more of an egg-dominant flavor rather than a sweet one. Definitely comparable to the versions I've had in Hong Kong, but I wouldn't call it better. Personally, I still prefer Portuguese egg tarts much more.

// Sesame Ball - 2 stars
I was so excited to purchase the most giant sesame ball I've ever seen. However, opening this sucker up was a huge let down as there was barely any red bean in it. 

// White Lotus Seed Paste Moon Cake - 4 stars
I really enjoyed this traditional moon cake! Wonderful flavors and smooth textures all throughout. If you've never had moon cakes before, this is a great classic option.

// Black Bean Moon Cake - 3 stars
Not sure I've heard of a black bean moon cake before, but it tasted just like red bean to me. In any case, the texture of this one was a little too chunky for my liking. 

// Strawberry Pie - 3 stars
The filling was mixed with strawberry flavored bits which added a nice crunch. It was pretty ordinary otherwise.

Egg. Tart. 

I like more egg custard in my tart, and the egg tart fairy has granted me this wish at Golden Gate Bakery! The egg tart is bigger and deeper than usual. The custard is ridiculously smooth, and the tart is crispy, but not full of oil and dough like other egg tarts. Always, always a line here, but worth the wait!

Oh and mama, who has lived in Hong Kong all her life, approves. And we all know mama knows best....(;

Delicious custard-y goodness. 

// LOCATION // Chinatown. Don't stress yourself out trying to find parking in these rambling hills and just use public transit. 

// WAIT // No line on a drizzly Saturday morning and we walked right in. 5 minutes later though, the line wrapped around the outside of the store. We made it in just in time!

// FOOD //
     +Egg Tart: So yummy. The outside was buttery and flake-y. The inside had a flan-like consistency and was delicious. It kept its form even as you ate away at the crust. 

I thought I grew out of egg tarts after years of dim sum restaurants during my childhood, but Golden Gate Bakery has rekindled our flame!

This summer, I went to SF at 4 times.  Each time I went to the store, they came up with a new sign.  "Closed for Vacation" and "Closed till 1 month from now".  Ahhhhh!  You got me all hooked on your famous eggtarts, then close on me for over a month!  Why?!?  You all aren't allowed to go on vacation at the same time.  You've got addicts out here just itching to get in your 1 hour lines for mooncakes and eggtarts.  T_T

One time, I was outside trying to get in and there was a "Vacation" sign on the door and this lady just stared at me as I tried to get in.  I fell to my knees and began crying and she just watched me like a honey badger!  I've got photos to prove it!  sad panda ;A;

They were closed all the time until my very last visit.  Ahh.  My cure to the madness.  Yummy mooncakes.  Too bad they ran out of yellow bean by the time I got into the store.  Oh well.  Date is almost as good but from GG Bakery, it was worth every minute standing in line. :D

the story goes (you know a friend heard it from a friend, who heard it from another friend, and so forth) that this place makes so many dan tat and has such great business they are free to have tons of holidays and just close up shop ... are you serious? yes. apparently, its true. their mooncakes (i have yet to try) make such great profit that they are just basking in their success.

dan tat, even if it was given to you later that day, its still freaking amazing. flaky and soft. eggs are not so sweet and fluffy. it just melts in your mouth like a harmonious symphony. 

if you buy one. you can't. you just can't! standing in the line, makes you need to get at least .. a few..... dozen =)
